12 A nonfiscal retirement bill shall include any retirement bill that
13 has as its sole purpose the appropriation or distribution or
14 redistribution of monies in some manner to a retirement system for
15 purposes of reducing the unfunded liability of such system or the
16 earmarking of a portion of the revenue from a tax to a retirement
17 system or increasing the percentage of the revenue earmarked from a
18 tax to a retirement system;
19 6. "Reduction-in-cost amendment" means an amendment to a
20 retirement bill having a fiscal impact which reduces the cost of the
21 bill as such cost is determined by the actuarial investigation for
22 the bill prepared pursuant to Section 3109 of this title;
23 7. "Retirement bill" means any bill or joint resolution
24 introduced or any bill or joint resolution amended by a member of
Req. No. 16490 Page 7

RBH No. 16490
1 the Legislature which creates or amends any law directly affecting a
2 retirement system. A retirement bill shall not mean a bill or
3 resolution that impacts the revenue of any state tax in which a
4 portion of the revenue generated from such tax is earmarked for the
5 benefit of a retirement system;
6 8. "Retirement bill having a fiscal impact" means any
7 retirement bill creating or establishing a retirement system and any
8 other retirement bill other than a nonfiscal retirement bill; and
9 9. "Retirement system" means the Teachers' Retirement System of
10 Oklahoma, the Oklahoma Public Employees Retirement System, the
11 Uniform Retirement System for Justices and Judges, the Oklahoma
12 Firefighters Pension and Retirement System, the Oklahoma Police
13 Pension and Retirement System, the Oklahoma Law Enforcement
14 Retirement System, or a retirement system established after January
15 1, 2006.
16 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 914.1 of Title 74, unless there
18 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. In lieu of terminating employment and accepting a service
20 retirement pension pursuant to Section 914 of this title, licensed
21 emergency medical personnel, as defined pursuant to Section 1-2503
22 of Title 63 of the Oklahoma Statutes, holding a license issued by
23 the State Department of Health pursuant to Section 1-2505 of Title
24 63 of the Oklahoma Statutes, including emergency medical responders,
Req. No. 16490 Page 8

RBH No. 16490
1 emer gency medical technicians, intermediate emergency medical
2 technicians, advanced emergency medical technicians, and paramedics
3 employed by any participating employer of the Oklahoma Public
4 Employees Retirement System as a licensed emergency medical
5 personnel and deputy sheriffs and county jailers employed by any
6 county that is a participating employer of the Oklahoma Public
7 Employees Retirement System who has not less than twenty (20) years
8 of creditable service and who is eligible to receive a service
9 retirement pension may make an irrevocable election to participate
10 in the Oklahoma Public Employees Deferred Option Plan and defer the
11 receipts of benefits in accordance with the provisions of this
12 section.
13 B. For purposes of this section, creditable service shall
14 include service credit reciprocally recognized pursuant to Section
15 901 et seq. of this title but for eligibility purposes only.
16 C. The duration of participation in the Oklahoma Public
17 Employees Deferred Option Plan for a member shall not exceed five
18 (5) years. Participation in the Oklahoma Public Employees Deferred
19 Option Plan must begin the first day of a month and end on the last
20 day of a month. At the conclusion of a member's participation in
21 the Oklahoma Public Employees Deferred Option Plan, the member shall
22 terminate employment with all participating employers or
23 participating municipalities, and shall start receiving the member's
24 accrued monthly retirement benefit from the System. Such a member
Req. No. 16490 Page 9

RBH No. 16490
1 may receive in-service distributions of such member's accrued
2 monthly retirement benefit from the System if such member is
3 reemployed by a participating employer only if such reemployment is
4 in a position not covered under the System.
5 D. When a member begins participation in the Oklahoma Public
6 Employees Deferred Option Plan, the contribution of the employee
7 shall cease. The employer contributions shall continue to be paid
8 in accordance with Section 920 or 920A of this title. Municipal
9 contributions for employees who elect the Oklahoma Public Employees
10 Deferred Option Plan shall be credited equally to the Oklahoma
11 Public Employees Retirement System and to the Oklahoma Public
12 Employees Deferred Option Plan. The monthly retirement benefits
13 that would have been payable had the member elected to cease
14 employment and receive a service retirement shall be paid into the
15 Oklahoma Public Employees Deferred Option Plan account.
16 E. A member who participates in this plan shall be eligible to
17 receive cost of living increases.
18 F. A participant in the Oklahoma Public Employees Deferred
19 Option Plan shall receive, at the option of the participant:
20 1. A lump sum payment from the account equal to the option
21 account balance of the participant, payable to the participant;
22 2. A lump sum payment from the account equal to the option
23 account balance of the participant, payable to the annuity provider
24
Req. No. 16490 Page 10

RBH No. 16490
1 whic h shall be selected by the participant as a result of the
2 research and investigation of the participant; or
3 3. Any other method of payment if approved by the Oklahoma
4 Public Employees Retirement System Board of Trustees.
5 Notwithstanding any other provision contained herein to the
6 contrary, commencement of distributions under the Oklahoma Public
7 Employees Deferred Option Plan shall be no later than the actual
8 retirement date of the member.
9 G. If the participant dies during the period of participation
10 in the Oklahoma Public Employees Deferred Option Plan, a lump sum
11 payment equal to the account balance of the participant shall be
12 paid to the recipients, which may include a trust, properly
13 designated in writing by the participant or, if none, to the
14 surviving spouse who was married to the participant for the thirty
15 (30) continuous months immediately preceding the death of the
16 participant; provided, a surviving spouse of a participant who died
17 in, and as a consequence of, the performance of the participant's
18 duty for a participating municipality shall not be subject to the
19 thirty-month marriage requirement for survivor benefits or, if no
20 surviving spouse, to the estate of the participant.
21 SECTION 3. Section 1 of this act shall become effective October
22 1, 2026.
